meanings.definition: To surpass in springing or leaping.
meanings.sent1: The young rabbit outsprung its siblings in the race.
meanings.sent2: The athlete outsprung all others in the long jump competition.
meanings.sent3: The frog outsprung the fish in the pond, surprising everyone.
meanings.sent4: Her joy outsprung like a fountain, bubbling over with excitement.
meanings.sent5: His energy outsprung from him like a coiled spring, propelling him forward.

meanings.sent1: The cat outsprung from behind the couch to catch the mouse.
meanings.sent2: The jack-in-the-box outsprung when the lid was lifted, startling the child.
meanings.sent3: The squirrel outsprung from the tree, landing gracefully on the ground.
meanings.sent4: Her laughter outsprung from her like a burst of confetti, filling the room with joy.
meanings.sent5: The idea outsprung in his mind like a spark, igniting his creativity.
